How2Say is a terminological exploring tool for multilingual corpora. 
<!--more-->
It allows to find for a given expression such as Pommes de terre:
the super terms « fécule de pomme de terre »
translation propositions for a target language « potatoes »
eventually some synonyms « papas (ES) »
How2Say works only with the terms used in the corpora. Consequently, it gives the most exact description of the terminological usage within a specific organization and/or a specific domain.
How2Say uses the corpora that can be aligned using the tools of myPREP from the Olanto Suite.

## Demo

Two demos are available:

* based on the DGT 2014 corpora of the european committee  (see [corpus]()https://ec.europa.eu/jrc/en/language-technologies/dgt-translation-memory) containing 85 million sentences from 24 languages.
* based on the UN corpora (MultiUN: A Multilingual corpus from United Nation Documents, Andreas Eisele and Yu Chen, [LREC 2010](https://www.dfki.de/lt/publication_show.php?id=4790)) containing 65 million sentences from 7 languages.

Start  [How2Say-MULTI-UN](https://88.127.130.21:5556/How2Say/how2say?query=pommes%20d%20terre&langso=FR&langta=EN)

Start  [How2Say-DGT2014](https://88.127.130.21:4444/How2Say/how2say?query=pommes%20d%20terre&langso=FR&langta=EN)
	
